Variables:
	PMT	payment
	PV	present value
	FV	future value
	N	number of periods
	I	interest rate per period
	k	1 if payment at end of perios, 1+I at beginning

PMT = ( PV + (PV + FV) / ( (1+I)^N - 1 ) ) . -I/k
FV = PMT . k / I - (1+I)^N . ( PV + PMT . k / I )
PV = ( PMT . k / I - FV ) / (1+I)^N - PMT . k / I

for N & I solve:
	0 = PV . (1+I)^N +  PMT . k . ( (1+I)^N - 1 ) / I  + FV
